THIRD TIME UPLOAD! 

What are some other brands you’d like to see #TarinisTopPicks from? 

This is not a sponsored video. I have recently been really impressed with some of @drsheths new launches.

Yes, not gonna deny. This brand has been under a lot of controversy in the past. Some of you also messaged me that they have got half filled bottles of their vitamin C serums. I hope the brand is listening to this feedback and working on it because I did see a lot for reviews claiming this. So far, personally I have found their products to be fully filled and effective. 

Their ingredients and formulations are brilliant and they are free of any fragrances, alcohol and the likes. Their price point is very competitive too. 

Disclaimer - These products were sent to me in PR to try out but I haven’t partnered with them for this video. The top picks are based on trying these products for several months on my own skin as well as on the basis of ingredients and formulations. 

Here’s a list of what I used: 

⏺Vitamin C Serum - Definitely one of my fav vitamin c serums. I have finished two bottles so far.  If 20% is too high for you, I recommend you begin with the 5% one from @pure_bubbles_skincare or the 10% one from @beminimalist__ 

⏺ Liquorice Lactic Acid Peel - I found this to be very brightening. The good thing about this is that it’s very customisable. You can use it for 5 mins or 10 mins or apply a thin layer overnight. I apply it as a 10 min facial peel and wash off. Perfect to lighten pigmentation or heal tanning. Recommended to use in the PM.

⏺ Aloe & Panthenol Hydrating Gel - This is great for healing a weak skin barrier and for hydrating oily skin without making it greasy.

⏺ Vitamin E and Ginseng Cream - This is a very moisturising cream.Recommend for normal, dry skin. For very dry skin, you may need to top this with an oil at nighttime. 

⏺ Niacinamide & Green Tea Toner - It’s an inexpensive toner but it’s also small in quantity. However, it’s effective, brightening and calming irritated, acne prone and oily skin.

#drsheths #indianskincare #indianskin #indianskincareblogger

A ‘must save’ post for sensitive skin! A lot of these are on some offers on the current Nykaa Pink Summer Sale, so I personally wouldn’t wait before stocking up on these. 

⏹️ Products featured: 

• @clinique_in Moisture Surge Serum - a milky blend of vitamin c, lactic acid and hyaluronic acid. It’s a fragrance free formulation much like the rest of the brand’s skincare. If you’re someone with dull, textured or dehydrated skin, this could be a game changer! I suggest using it at night to begin with, but it can also be used under sunscreen in the day. 
• ⁠@drjart_india’s Cicapair Soothing Repair Mask was something I didn’t expect to like so much. I’ve not been a fan of gel overnight masks. I much prefer creams, but this one surprised me and how! It’s SO SO soothing. Comforts my skin on redness and breakout days, even on days I have tiny pimples around my nose, and just gives it a glow the next day. Perfect for summer and apart for sensitive 
 sensitive, it’ll also work beautifully for acne prone oily skin! 
• @theordinary’s 5% Niacinamide Emulsion was a launch I’ve waited for, for a long time! I’ve loved their 10% Niacinamide serum much like many others but I know it didn’t work for many of you, hence this 5% one would be perfect for sensitive skin that has large pores, oiliness and uneven skin tone. Can also be used for body pigmentation. 

Disclaimer - All of these products are safe for pregnant and breastfeeding mothers as per me, but please check with your doctor to be safe, and patch test before use.

#wishlinked

I feel like our moms, aunts and grand moms had such little knowledge growing up on what to do for their skin, but now that there is so much information available, it can be overwhelming for them as to where to get started, so I wanted to make this video for those women, who spent a large part of their lives raising their kids, being there for their family and putting themselves last, and not having enough time to take care of themselves. 

Well, it’s never too late to have a sustainable, effective skincare routine, so this is for the women in their 50s and 60s! Hope this video helps you to build a routine for yourselves. If you have questions drop them down below and if you need any links, just comment ‘link’ and they’ll automatically be in your DMs. 

Note that this routine is particularly for my mother’s skin type and concern which is dry skin with pigmentation and fine lines.
